President Obama expresses his condolences to the family and community of Michael Brown, who recently passed away. He acknowledges that the Department of Justice is investigating the situation and will continue to support it as necessary. The President urges people to reflect on the events and to engage in healing conversations rather than harmful ones. He emphasizes the importance of comforting one another and treating each other with understanding. The President believes that this is what Michael and his family, as well as the broader American community, deserve.